6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Both MEXC and BingX use standard 8-hour funding intervals with rates calculated from price premiums to spot markets. MEXC's zero maker fees create better entry/exit conditions for funding rate arbitrage, while BingX's higher fees reduce net profitability. MEXC typically lists more volatile altcoins earlier, potentially offering higher funding rates but with increased liquidation risks. BingX focuses on established pairs with more predictable funding patterns but lower absolute rates."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lb",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange offers better funding rate arbitrage opportunities?","answer":"MEXC provides superior opportunities due to zero maker fees and early listings of high-volatility tokens. The fee advantage alone can improve arbitrage returns by 0.02% per trade cycle compared to BingX."},{"question":"How do funding rate calculations differ between MEXC and BingX?","answer":"Both exchanges use similar 8-hour funding mechanisms based on perpetual-spot price premiums. However, MEXC's thinner order books can create more volatile funding rates, while BingX's rates tend to be more stable due to lower overall trading activity."},{"question":"What are the liquidity differences for funding rate strategies?","answer":"MEXC generally offers higher liquidity for major pairs but can have thin books for newer listings. BingX provides more consistent liquidity across its limited pair selection, making position sizing more predictable for systematic strategies."},{"question":"Which platform has more reliable funding rate data and execution?","answer":"BingX offers more reliable execution and transparent volume reporting, while MEXC's aggressive growth strategy has led to concerns about volume authenticity. For consistent funding rate strategies, BingX provides more dependable infrastructure despite higher costs."}]}]
